<p><i><b>A Scanner Darkly</b></i> is a 1977 <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novel</a> by <a href="/wiki/Philip_K._Dick" title="Philip K. Dick">Philip K. Dick</a>. The semi-<a href="/wiki/Autobiography" title="Autobiography">autobiographical</a> story is set in a <a href="/wiki/Dystopia" title="Dystopia">dystopian</a> <a href="/wiki/Orange_County,_California" title="Orange County, California">Orange County, California</a> in the then-future of June 1994. It includes an extensive portrayal of <a href="/wiki/Drug_culture" title="Drug culture" class="mw-redirect">drug culture</a> and <a href="/wiki/Drug_use" title="Drug use">drug use</a>.</p>
